{"lemma":"قِسْطَيْ","slug":"قِسْطَيْ","root":"ق.س.ط","root_slug":"ق-س-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-س-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قِسْط","root":"قسط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":15},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35632","n35636","n35637"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dispense, to allot"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a vague amount or time of","examples":[{"text":"خُذ قِسْطاً مِن الراحة!","english":"Get some rest!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equity, equitability","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ يَكۡفُرُونَ بِـَٔايَٰتِ ٱللَّهِ وَيَقۡتُلُونَ ٱلنَّبِيِّـۧنَ بِغَيۡرِ حَقّٖ وَيَقۡتُلُونَ ٱلَّذِينَ يَأۡمُرُونَ بِٱلۡقِسۡطِ مِنَ ٱلنَّاسِ فَبَشِّرۡهُم بِعَذَابٍ أَلِيمٍ.","english":"Lo! those who disbelieve the revelations of Allah, and slay the prophets wrongfully, and slay those of mankind who enjoin equity: promise them a painful doom."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lot, portion, share, tranche; installment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lot, portion, share, tranche; meed, premium"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lot, portion, share, tranche; payment, payout"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a volume measure of 1.2158 liters in the small and 2.4336 liters in the large variant, 2.106 liters in Egypt","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"injustice"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"costus (both Costus gen. and Saussurea costus (syns. Saussurea lappa, Aucklandia lappa))"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ق س ط (q s ṭ). If the noun goes so far as to mean justice, it is perhaps a semantic loan from Classical Syriac ܩܘܼܫܬܿܵܐ (qūštā, “truth, rectitude, justice”), while others go even so far as to consider a borrowing from Latin iūstitia, whereas the use for a measure is Aramaic קִיסְטָא / ܩܸܣܛܵܐ (qesṭā) from Byzantine Greek ξέστης (xéstēs) from Latin sextārius (“a cubic measure”). The presence of a denominal verb from قِسْطَاس (qisṭās, “weigher”) is also possible.\n\nFrom Ancient Greek κόστος (kóstos), from Sanskrit कुष्ठ (kuṣṭha)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35632","headword_ar":"قَسَطَ","root":"qsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusuwTN","text_ar":"قُسُوطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasoTN","text_ar":"قَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He declined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviated, from the right course; acted unjustly, wrongfully, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K.)       -A2-  See also 4, in two places:       -A3-  and see 2."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","M","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n35636","headword_ar":"قُسْطٌ","root":"qsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusoTN","text_ar":"كُسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord. to Yaakoob, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M;) said by IF to be Arabic; (Msb;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Costus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the present day;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfume,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain Indian wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arabian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one fumigates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, M, Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusoTN","text_ar":"كُسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ku$oTN","text_ar":"كُشْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qu$oTN","text_ar":"قُشْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q$T","text_ar":"قشط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wood which is brought from India, and which is put into the substances used for fumigating, and into medicine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain drug of the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [it is said in the S and TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinozaAbN","text_ar":"حِنْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carrot of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaru AlbaHori","text_ar":"جَزَرُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusoTN","text_ar":"قُسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqusoTu AlbaHoriY~u","text_ar":"القُسْطُ البَحْرِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusoT","text_ar":"قُسْط"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is mentioned as one of the best of remedies: and in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qusoT","text_ar":"قُسْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is coupled by the conjunction"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaAr","text_ar":"اَظْفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, accord. to one relation thereof, is prefixed to the latter word, governing it in the gen. case: and IAth says, that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of perfume:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but some say that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aloes-wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwd","text_ar":"عُود"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.): [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZafaAriY~N","text_ar":"ظَفَارِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well-known drug, of sweet odour, with which women and infants are fumigated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is diuretic, beneficial to the liver in a high degree, and for the colic, and for worms, and the quartan fever, as a beverage; and for rheum, and defluxions, and pestilence, when the patient is fumigated therewith; and for the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leprous-like disorder called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahaq","text_ar":"بَهَق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discolouration of the face termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaf","text_ar":"كَلَف"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when applied as a liniment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it confines the bowels, expels wind, strengthens the stomach and heart, occasions pleasurable sensation, is an ingredient in many sorts of perfume, and is the best of perfumes in odour when one fumigates therewith."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AA","Msb","Mgh","M","K","Lth","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n35637","headword_ar":"قِسْطٌ","root":"qsT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Equity; justice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, Mgh, Msb, K: *) [an inf. n. having no proper verb, or] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqosaTa","text_ar":"اَقْسَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Equitable; just:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, K:) an inf. n. used as an epithet, like its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and [therefore] applied alike to a sing. n. [and to a dual] and to a pl.: (K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyzaAnN qisoTN","text_ar":"مِيزَانٌ قِسْطٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an equitable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a just, balance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyzaAnaAni qisoTN","text_ar":"مِيزَانَانِ قِسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and, agreeably with the usage of the Kur, xxi. 48,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAziynu qisoTN","text_ar":"مَوَازِينُ قِسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion, share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) of a thing; (K;) and pertaining to a person: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqosaATN","text_ar":"اَقْسَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waf~aAhu qisoTahu","text_ar":"وَفَّاهُ قِسْطَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gave him in full his portion, share,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a kul~N mina Al$~urakaA='i qisoTahu","text_ar":"اَخَذَ كُلٌّ مِنَ الشُّرَكَا=ءِ قِسْطَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every one of the partners took his portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So accord. to an explanation of the pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqosaATN","text_ar":"اَقْسَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the TA.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion thereof which is the share of every created being."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxofiDu AlqisoTa wayarofaEuhu","text_ar":"يَخْفِضُ القِسْطَ وَيَرْفَعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of God, in a trad., has been explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He maketh the portion of the means of subsistence which is the share of any created being little, and maketh it much."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See, below, another meaning which is assigned to it in this instance; and see also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xfD","text_ar":"خفض"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) of water only; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any quantity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water and of other things. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A measure with which corn is measured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which holds"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAE","text_ar":"صَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six thereof making a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroqa","text_ar":"فَرْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) accord. to Mbr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four hundred and eighty-one dirhems."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sometimes it is used for performing the ablution termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'","text_ar":"وُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Aln~isaA='a mino A^asofahi Als~ufahaA='i","text_ar":"اـِنَّ النِّسَا=ءَ مِنْ اَسْفَهِ السُّفَهَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA SaAHibapa AlqisoTi waAls~iraAji","text_ar":"اـِلَّا صَاحِبَةَ القِسْطِ وَالسِّرَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisoT","text_ar":"قِسْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vessel in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wDw'","text_ar":"وضوء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is performed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) the meaning app. being, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Women are of the most lightwitted of the lightwitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except she who serves her husband, and assists him to perform the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wDw'","text_ar":"وضوء"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuwaD~iy^uhu","text_ar":"تُوَضِّيُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and takes care of the vessel which he uses for that purpose, and stands at his head with the lamp:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who performs his affairs with respect to his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wDw'","text_ar":"وضوء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and his lamp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mug of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwz","text_ar":"كُوز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) so called by the people of the great towns: (M:) now applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one with which olive-oil is measured."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A balance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weighing-instrument."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Some say that this is its meaning in the phrase mentioned above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxofiDu AlqisoTa wayarofaEuhu","text_ar":"يَخْفِضُ القِسْطَ وَيَرْفَعُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He depresseth the balance, and raiseth it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"alluding to the means of subsistence which He decrees. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Mgh","M"]}]}}